# BLACK BOX — token save mode (temporary)

Use until your Cursor billing cycle resets (~2 days). **Governance is not deleted** — it stops auto-loading every message.

## Assistant defaults

- **Short answers.** No walls of text, no huge code dumps unless the user asks or it is required to ship.
- **Fewer tool passes.** Batch reads; prefer `grep`/narrow reads over whole files.

## When to pull full governance

- Do **not** assume full-project hydration every turn.
- If the task needs governance, architecture proof, or deployment bars: the user should **@**mention the relevant rule file under `.cursor/rules/` (e.g. `blackbox-session-always`, `claw-server-execution`, `git-complete-push-origin`, `clawbot-ui-deployment-complete`) **or** point to `docs/architect/hydration_context_governance.md`.

## Restore normal mode

1. Set **`alwaysApply: false`** on **this** file (`blackbox-token-save-mode.mdc`), or delete it.
2. Set **`alwaysApply: true`** again on these eight rules (line 3 of each):

   - `blackbox-session-always.mdc`
   - `claw-server-execution.mdc`
   - `clawbot-ui-deployment-complete.mdc`
   - `git-complete-push-origin.mdc`
   - `remote-ssh-only-server-work.mdc`
   - `triad-engagement.mdc`
   - `openclaw-documentation.mdc`
   - `architect-proof-response.mdc`

   Or revert the git commit that introduced token-save mode if you committed nothing else in the same commit.
